139
00:12:34.211 --> 00:12:35.463 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s right around the corner.

140
00:12:35.546 --> 00:12:37.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But if you two fell back in love now,

141
00:12:37.965 --> 00:12:39.800 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Hachi would be stuck
in an impossible situation!

142
00:12:39.884 --> 00:12:41.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course she’s scared!

143
00:12:44.680 --> 00:12:46.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All the more reason
why I shouldn’t see her.

144
00:12:47.057 --> 00:12:48.601 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can’t you just get stuck with her?

145
00:12:59.778 --> 00:13:00.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Forget it.

146
00:13:02.239 --> 00:13:04.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
After all, you probably just wanted
to comfort Hachi

147
00:13:04.116 --> 00:13:06.952 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
who had been dumped by her old boyfriend

148
00:13:07.036 --> 00:13:08.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and was being used by Takumi.

149
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:11.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You never really loved her.
-I do love her!

150
00:13:11.707 --> 00:13:12.791 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What do you know?

151
00:13:12.875 --> 00:13:15.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But now you love
that girl next door, right?

152
00:13:15.920 --> 00:13:19.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hear that girl has
the same condition as me.

153
00:13:19.465 --> 00:13:22.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She can’t even go to work
without her medication.

154
00:13:22.426 --> 00:13:26.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So what?
She’s trying her best in spite of that!

155
00:13:28.015 --> 00:13:31.602 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Since long ago,
you’ve always loved helpless girls

156
00:13:31.685 --> 00:13:35.731 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
who are stuck in some sort of situation
you had absolutely nothing to do with.

157
00:13:36.732 --> 00:13:39.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That way, you can always play
the part of the hero, right?

158
00:13:40.528 --> 00:13:41.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nana, cut it out.

159
00:13:41.695 --> 00:13:44.657 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But then, the moment you feel
you’re being pulled in,

160
00:13:44.740 --> 00:13:46.659 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you let go of her hand.

161
00:13:46.742 --> 00:13:50.037 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Nobu, she’s just provoking you.
Don’t mind her.

162
00:13:57.336 --> 00:13:59.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What an easygoing form of love.</i>

163
00:14:13.852 --> 00:14:17.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nana can be really cruel.

164
00:14:17.356 --> 00:14:21.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
She’s purposely trying to push them
into an impossible situation.

165
00:14:21.527 --> 00:14:22.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course Nobu would react

166
00:14:22.987 --> 00:14:25.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and get serious from the way
he was confronted.

167
00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:28.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hachi’s gonna end up suffering even more.

168
00:14:31.328 --> 00:14:34.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nobu is a pacifist.

169
00:14:34.164 --> 00:14:37.710 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He’s always tried his hardest to choose

170
00:14:37.793 --> 00:14:41.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the path that would make everyone happy.

171
00:14:42.548 --> 00:14:46.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don’t think trying to avoid conflict
is the same as being easygoing.

172
00:14:50.222 --> 00:14:51.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I agree.

173
00:14:52.516 --> 00:14:56.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
After all, it’s a battle
against his own desires.

174
00:15:03.027 --> 00:15:04.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What would you like?

175
00:15:05.029 --> 00:15:06.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Miss? How many do you want?

176
00:15:08.198 --> 00:15:09.158 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Three.

177
00:15:20.377 --> 00:15:23.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I’ll do everything I can</i>
<i>to make you happy.</i>

178
00:15:46.362 --> 00:15:49.198 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I wanna see you, Hachiko.</i>

179
00:15:52.826 --> 00:15:54.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So hurry.</i>

180
00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:05.047 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>If you two fell back in love now,</i>

181
00:16:05.130 --> 00:16:07.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Hachi would be stuck</i>
<i>in an impossible situation.</i>

182
00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It’s been a while
since I’ve seen fireworks.

183
00:16:26.986 --> 00:16:28.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They sure are pretty.

184
00:16:28.570 --> 00:16:30.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This is the first time I’ve ever had
food from a food stand.

185
00:16:30.948 --> 00:16:32.074 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What?
-What?

186
00:16:32.866 --> 00:16:34.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It’s pretty good!

187
00:16:34.702 --> 00:16:37.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But it’s hard to eat with chopsticks.

188
00:16:38.205 --> 00:16:40.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wonder if any of the stands have forks.

189
00:16:40.165 --> 00:16:42.334 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
D-- Don’t spoil him! Make him practice!

190
00:16:42.418 --> 00:16:43.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don’t grab me so suddenly!

191
00:16:43.711 --> 00:16:45.212 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
My wig will shift!

192
00:16:45.295 --> 00:16:46.130 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
HACHI

193
00:16:47.923 --> 00:16:49.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Your wig!
-Hello?

194
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:52.636 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Shin?
-<i>Yeah, what is it?</i>

195
00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:55.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm at the apartment,
but no one’s answering.

196
00:16:56.306 --> 00:16:58.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Have you all gone ahead</i>
<i>to see the fireworks?</i>

197
00:17:01.937 --> 00:17:03.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>But the light’s on in the room.</i>

198
00:17:04.023 --> 00:17:05.357 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Where are you?</i>

199
00:17:06.316 --> 00:17:07.359 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Shin?</i>

200
00:17:09.319 --> 00:17:13.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah. We couldn’t wait
any longer and left. Sorry.

201
00:17:14.575 --> 00:17:17.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I should be the one apologizing
for being late.

202
00:17:17.745 --> 00:17:21.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ll head over there right now.
Where are you watching it from?

203
00:17:22.833 --> 00:17:25.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yeah. Got it.
I’ll call again if I can’t find you.

204
00:17:27.212 --> 00:17:28.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What? You’re dressed as a girl?

205
00:17:46.690 --> 00:17:49.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Can’t you just get stuck with her?</i>

206
00:17:58.702 --> 00:18:01.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>What an easygoing form of love.</i>

207
00:18:02.247 --> 00:18:03.415 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Over here!

208
00:18:03.499 --> 00:18:05.918 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? No way! Shin? You’re so cute!

209
00:18:06.001 --> 00:18:07.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on! Everyone’s here.

210
00:18:11.757 --> 00:18:14.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They’re so pretty! Awesome!

211
00:18:15.052 --> 00:18:16.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They really are pretty, aren’t they?

212
00:18:16.720 --> 00:18:20.641 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, Shin.
You’re sounding like Misato!

213
00:18:21.767 --> 00:18:23.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What a huge diamond.

214
00:18:24.269 --> 00:18:30.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, Nobu aside, why aren’t you
inviting me to your wedding?

215
00:18:30.317 --> 00:18:31.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You did invite Yasu and Shin.

216
00:18:31.902 --> 00:18:33.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh? You’d come?

217
00:18:33.695 --> 00:18:35.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Of course I would.

218
00:18:35.697 --> 00:18:38.367 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’ll even sing you the punk version
of Ladybugs’ "Samba".

219
00:18:38.450 --> 00:18:40.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What’s that? What kind of song is it?

220
00:18:40.202 --> 00:18:42.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I’ll buy you the CD

221
00:18:42.329 --> 00:18:43.956 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so you can arrange it
and play the guitar part.

222
00:18:44.039 --> 00:18:46.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You be happy, no matter what, okay?

223
00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:53.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nobu stepped aside so that you’d be happy.

224
00:18:53.340 --> 00:18:57.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So if you end up unhappy,
it was for nothing.

225
00:18:59.972 --> 00:19:02.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, with Takumi as your husband,

226
00:19:02.641 --> 00:19:05.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I’m sure he’s gonna make you cry
from time to time.

227
00:19:05.561 --> 00:19:07.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But you’re the fool who fell
in love with him,

228
00:19:07.354 --> 00:19:08.397 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so that can’t be helped.

229
00:19:10.023 --> 00:19:13.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And don’t get discouraged when he cheats
on you now and then, all right?

230
00:19:13.986 --> 00:19:17.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just smack him around
until you feel better.

231
00:19:21.285 --> 00:19:24.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah. You’re right.

232
00:19:25.831 --> 00:19:28.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, Nana.

233
00:19:32.254 --> 00:19:36.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That day, the riverside was packed</i>
<i>with people,</i>

234
00:19:36.842 --> 00:19:39.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and I never saw Shoji and his girlfriend.</i>

235
00:19:41.138 --> 00:19:44.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I felt that the curtain had finally</i>
<i>come down on our relationship.</i>

236
00:19:45.976 --> 00:19:46.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>There was such a big crowd</i>

237
00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:49.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>that you could easily lose sight</i>
<i>of the people you were with.</i>

238
00:19:50.063 --> 00:19:53.025 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>So I wanted to hold Nana’s hand…</i>

239
00:19:53.108 --> 00:19:55.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>But I was worried she’d think</i>
<i>I’m insensitive</i>

240
00:19:55.444 --> 00:19:59.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>if I innocently grabbed her hand,</i>
<i>which was as warm as Nobu’s.</i>

241
00:20:01.533 --> 00:20:04.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The wind blowing on my fingertips</i>
<i>was freezing cold.</i>

242
00:20:05.787 --> 00:20:09.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Come to think of it,</i>
<i>summer ended long ago, didn’t it?</i>

243
00:20:14.546 --> 00:20:16.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did you guys have fun at the fireworks?

244
00:20:16.965 --> 00:20:19.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Get ready to continue working hard!

245
00:20:20.510 --> 00:20:21.511 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh?

246
00:20:32.481 --> 00:20:33.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hey, Nana.</i>

247
00:20:35.025 --> 00:20:38.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>That summer you longed for</i>
<i>more than anyone,</i>

248
00:20:38.278 --> 00:20:42.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>the one we couldn’t get back,</i>
<i>is right here.</i>

249
00:20:43.492 --> 00:20:45.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I’ll always be waiting.</i>

250
00:20:46.119 --> 00:20:51.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>For ten years… twenty years… fifty years…</i>

251
00:22:15.334 --> 00:22:16.752 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Hey, Nana…</i>

